{"type":"message","id":"cab4cb52","parentId":"c190340a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:20:00.982Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_syxnieyhy708_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 091914\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and pending items:\r\n\r\n1. **TIC Experiment** is the next action - implementing Temporal Invariance Compression classifier on pulse logs\r\n2. The goal is to test on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n3. Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete task that requires:\r\n1. Reading the pulse log files\r\n2. Implementing a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Testing prediction of next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse logs exist and start implementing this experiment.\r\n\r\nLooking at the notes:\r\n- Recent pulse: `pulse_2026-03-24 091814.md`\r\n- The doc `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md` has the hypothesis\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. Check what pulse logs exist\r\n2. Create a TIC experiment script that analyzes the logs\r\n3. Implement the invariant/variant classifier\r\n\r\nLet me write a PowerShell script for the TIC experiment that will:\r\n1. Load recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identify invariant patterns (things that persist across pulses)\r\n3. Identify variant patterns (things that change)\r\n4. Test prediction accuracy on next pulse\r\n\r\nThis advances Phase 1 by testing the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant content across pulse logs and tests next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment script that analyzes pulse logs, classifies invariant/variant content, and measures prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Tests compression-causal duality: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$lookback = 10,\r\n    [string]$logDir = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# --- Configuration ---\r\n$COMPRESSION_THRESHOLD = 0.7  # λ parameter\r\n$CLASSIFICATION_TARGET = 0.70\r\n$PREDICTION_TARGET = 0.60\r\n\r\n# --- Helper Functions ---\r\nfunction Get-PulseLogs {\r\n    param([int]$count)\r\n    Get-ChildItem -Path $logDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" |\r\n        Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending |\r\n        Select-Object -First $count\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Extract-ContentBlocks {\r\n    param([string]$content)\r\n    # Split into semantic blocks (paragraphs, lists, code blocks)\r\n    $blocks = @()\r\n    $lines = $content -split \"`n\"\r\n    $currentBlock = \"\"\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($line in $lines) {\r\n        if ($line -match '^\\s*$' -and $currentBlock -ne \"\") {\r\n            if ($currentBlock.Trim().Length -gt 10) {\r\n                $blocks += $currentBlock.Trim()\r\n            }\r\n            $currentBlock = \"\"\r\n        } else {\r\n            $currentBlock += \" $line\"\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    if ($currentBlock.Trim().Length -gt 10) {\r\n        $blocks += $currentBlock.Trim()\r\n    }\r\n    return $blocks\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Get-NGramHash {\r\n    param([string]$text, [int]$n = 3)\r\n    $words = $text -split '\\s+' | Where-Object { $_.Length -gt 2 }\r\n    $ngrams = @()\r\n    for ($i = 0; $i -lt ($words.Count - $n + 1); $i++) {\r\n        $ngram = ($words[$i..($i + $n - 1)] -join \" \").ToLower()\r\n        $ngrams += $ngram\r\n    }\r\n    return $ngrams\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Measure-Invariance {\r\n    param([array]$blocks, [hashtable]$globalPatternFreq)\r\n    \r\n    $results = @()\r\n    foreach ($block in $blocks) {\r\n        $ngrams = Get-NGramHash -text $block\r\n        $matchCount = 0\r\n        $totalNgrams = $ngrams.Count\r\n        \r\n        foreach ($ngram in $ngrams) {\r\n            if ($globalPatternFreq.ContainsKey($ngram)) {\r\n                $matchCount++\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        $invarianceScore = if ($totalNgrams -gt 0) { $matchCount / $totalNgrams } else { 0 }\r\n        \r\n        $results += @{\r\n            Block = $block.Substring(0, [Math]::Min(100, $block.Length))\r\n            InvarianceScore = $invarianceScore\r\n            Classification = if ($invarianceScore -ge $COMPRESSION_THRESHOLD) { \"INVARIANT\" } else { \"VARIANT\" }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    return $results\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Predict-NextPulse {\r\n    param([array]$invariantPatterns, [array]$variantPatterns, [string]$nextContent)\r\n    \r\n    $invNgrams = @{}\r\n    foreach ($pat in $invariantPatterns) {\r\n        foreach ($ngram in (Get-NGramHash -text $pat)) {\r\n            $invNgrams[$ngram] = $true\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $nextNgrams = Get-NGramHash -text $nextContent\r\n    $predictedCount = 0\r\n    foreach ($ngram in $nextNgrams) {\r\n        if ($invNgrams.ContainsKey($ngram)) {\r\n            $predictedCount++\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return if ($nextNgrams.Count -gt 0) { $predicted\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:19:47\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774358400981}}
